title: For Sale:  Free Market Guns?
postcontent:
Regulated guns affect both private and retail sales prices. We are seeing this now with private sales up due to the threat of a ban (regulation). Subsidies affect the prices in both retail and private sales. Subsides cause subsidised brands to be cheaper that they would be for competition that is not subsidized (at the tax payers expence).  It affects prices that people pay for them at all levels because the products enter the market at an artifcially low price.
I'll give the definition of "free market" one more time and if anyone still thinks private gun sales are not "restrained by government interferance, regulation or subsidy"...then so be it.
This is not a blog so I'll quit posting....just can't stand the free market getting blamed for high prices. If the market were actually free gun owners would be enjoying more guns at much cheaper prices.
Have a great day and happy shooting! Check out Milton Friedman for more info about how free markets work! 

free market 

Definitions (3)

1. Business governed by the laws of supply and demand, not restrained by government interference, regulation or subsidy.

2. A foreign exchange market that is not controlled by the government.

3. A security with sufficient liquidity that its price is not significantly affected by availability.


Read more: http://www.investorwords.com/2086/free_market.html#ixzz2HW0Jvegx
